Perhaps the birds are sedentary in the Greater Antilles[2]. On the islands of Cuba, Jamaica and Haiti, birds can remain all winter, sometimes flying to Guyana in the north of South America. During the breeding season from April to September, birds are often observed on the islands Guadeloupe,
