 Dominica and Martinique, and extremely rarely on the islands of Puerto Rico, St. Lucia, St. Vincent, Montserrat, Barbados and Grenada [11]. Birds were recorded in Puerto Rico from March-April to August-September, in June in Guyana and in July on the island of Trinidad[2]. Migration
The exact wintering grounds of the black american swift are unknown.